# Shadcn UI

**Objective**: Standardize the integration and extension of Shadcn UI components to ensure consistency and maintainability.

**Context**: To apply for standardizing the use of this technology in projects.

## Explanation

Shadcn UI is the foundation of the design system. Components are installed locally via CLI and can be customized according to project needs.

**Key Principles:**

- **Local installation**: components are copied to `src/components/ui/` via CLI.
- **Customization**: components can be modified after installation.
- **Consistency**: respect Shadcn UI structure and conventions for custom components.
- **Variants**: use `cva()` to manage variants.
- **Accessibility**: all Shadcn components are accessible by default (ARIA).

**Installing a component:**

```bash
npx shadcn@latest add button
npx shadcn@latest add input
npx shadcn@latest add dialog
```

**Structure :**

```
src/components/ui/
 ├─ button.tsx
 ├─ input.tsx
 ├─ dialog.tsx
 ├─ card.tsx
 └─ index.ts
```

## Practical Implementation Example

**Using a Shadcn component:**

```tsx
import { Button } from "@/components/ui/button";
import { Input } from "@/components/ui/input";

export function LoginForm() {
  return (
    <form className="space-y-4">
      <Input type="email" placeholder="Email" />
      <Input type="password" placeholder="Password" />
      <Button type="submit">Sign In</Button>
    </form>
  );
}
```

**Customizing a Shadcn component:**

```tsx
// src/components/ui/button.tsx (après installation)
import * as React from "react";
import { cva, type VariantProps } from "class-variance-authority";
import { cn } from "@/lib/utils";

const buttonVariants = cva(
  "inline-flex items-center justify-center rounded-md font-medium transition-colors focus-visible:outline-none disabled:pointer-events-none disabled:opacity-50",
  {
    variants: {
      variant: {
        default: "bg-primary-500 text-white hover:bg-primary-600",
        destructive: "bg-red-500 text-white hover:bg-red-600",
        outline: "border border-gray-300 bg-transparent hover:bg-gray-100",
        ghost: "hover:bg-gray-100",
        link: "text-primary-500 underline-offset-4 hover:underline",
      },
      size: {
        default: "h-10 px-4 py-2",
        sm: "h-9 px-3",
        lg: "h-11 px-8",
        icon: "h-10 w-10",
      },
    },
    defaultVariants: {
      variant: "default",
      size: "default",
    },
  }
);

export interface ButtonProps
  extends React.ButtonHTMLAttributes<HTMLButtonElement>,
    VariantProps<typeof buttonVariants> {
  asChild?: boolean;
}

export const Button = React.forwardRef<HTMLButtonElement, ButtonProps>(
  ({ className, variant, size, ...props }, ref) => {
    return (
      <button
        className={cn(buttonVariants({ variant, size, className }))}
        ref={ref}
        {...props}
      />
    );
  }
);
Button.displayName = "Button";
```

**Creating a custom component in Shadcn style:**

```tsx
// src/components/ui/stat-card.tsx
import * as React from "react";
import { cva, type VariantProps } from "class-variance-authority";
import { cn } from "@/lib/utils";

const statCardVariants = cva(
  "rounded-lg border bg-white p-6 shadow-sm dark:bg-gray-800",
  {
    variants: {
      variant: {
        default: "border-gray-200 dark:border-gray-700",
        success: "border-green-200 bg-green-50 dark:border-green-700 dark:bg-green-900",
        danger: "border-red-200 bg-red-50 dark:border-red-700 dark:bg-red-900",
      },
    },
    defaultVariants: {
      variant: "default",
    },
  }
);

export interface StatCardProps
  extends React.HTMLAttributes<HTMLDivElement>,
    VariantProps<typeof statCardVariants> {
  title: string;
  value: string | number;
  icon?: React.ReactNode;
}

export function StatCard({
  className,
  variant,
  title,
  value,
  icon,
  ...props
}: StatCardProps) {
  return (
    <div className={cn(statCardVariants({ variant, className }))} {...props}>
      <div className="flex items-center justify-between">
        <div>
          <p className="text-sm font-medium text-gray-600 dark:text-gray-400">
            {title}
          </p>
          <p className="text-2xl font-bold">{value}</p>
        </div>
        {icon && <div className="text-gray-400">{icon}</div>}
      </div>
    </div>
  );
}
```

## Variants or Exceptions

- Very feature-specific components can remain in `features/[name]/components/`.
- Existing projects can use other UI libraries but should progressively migrate to Shadcn UI.

